<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is named after the renowned writer in Malayalam poetry, who stood with her strong words for mother Nature and conservation of natural resources, Padmasree Smt. Sugathakumari. She was at the forefront of environmental and feminist movements in 
<collectingRegion box="[763,838,230,256]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Kerala</collectingRegion>
and played a prominent role in the save Silent Valley movement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,498,302,328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—So far, the new species is collected only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1108,1156,303,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
locality of Mattumala, in Nelliyampathy hills of 
<collectingRegion box="[395,470,338,364]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Kerala</collectingRegion>
at an elevation of 
<quantity box="[676,830,338,365]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="1100.0">1100–1200 m</quantity>
a.s.l. 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1199,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tripogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sugathakumariae">
<emphasis box="[896,1199,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Tripogon sugathakumariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found growing in open montane grasslands along with 
<taxonomicName authority="Roemer &amp; Schultes" authorityName="Roemer &amp; Schultes" authorityYear="1817" box="[547,915,374,401]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tripogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bromoides">
<emphasis box="[547,690,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">T. bromoides</emphasis>
Roemer &amp; Schultes
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1753: 745) De Candolle (1825: 352)" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityPageNumber="352" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="745" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Alysicarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bupleurifolius">
<emphasis box="[968,1263,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Alysicarpus bupleurifolius</emphasis>
